---
// /for-chiros/ — chiropractors and physiotherapists vertical lander
// Lead feature per ICP research: Win-Back / Reactivation Sequences
// (Jane App handles reminders; the bleeding wound is silent fade-out of patients)
// Persona language: rebookings, reactivations, care plans, ROF, the 3 R's, MVA, WSIB.
// Trust signals: OCA / OPA membership, College advertising rules respected.

import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="For chiropractors &amp; physiotherapists — Reactivate, rebook, retain"
  description="AI customer lifecycle for GTA chiro and physio practices. Reactivate inactive patients, fix the 5-minute lead response, finish care plans, automate rebookings. Jane App-native. Done-for-you. From $1,497/mo."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="ai-hero">
    <p class="ai-eyebrow">FOR GTA CHIROPRACTORS &amp; PHYSIOTHERAPISTS</p>
    <h1>Your patients drop off after visit 4.<br>We bring them back.</h1>
    <p class="ai-lead">
      Most GTA chiro and physio practices on Jane App have 200–400 patients who haven't been in for 90+ days.
      Care plan completion sits below 60%. New leads from Google or Instagram wait 24 hours for a response —
      MIT data says 1 hour or less means 7× the conversion.
    </p>
    <p class="ai-lead" style="font-weight:600;color:var(--tx);">
      We run rebookings, reactivations, and lead response on autopilot. From $1,497/mo. Jane App–native.
    </p>
    <div class="ai-cta-row">
      <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a free audit →</a>
      <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="/services/">See pricing</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pain bullets -->
  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap ai-narrow">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow">Sound like your practice?</p>
      <h2>The 3 R's are quietly broken.</h2>
      <ul class="ai-painlist" style="font-size:17px;margin-top:24px;">
        <li>"Patients drop off after the third visit. We never reach back out."</li>
        <li>"Half my new patient leads ghost between the consult and the first appointment."</li>
        <li>"My front desk is part-time / my front desk is my wife. Things slip."</li>
        <li>"I know we should be running reactivations every month. We don't."</li>
        <li>"Care plan completion is well under 60%. I don't even track it."</li>
        <li>"One bad Google review last quarter and we have nothing to bury it with."</li>
        <li>"Direct billing reconciliation is killing me. So is the 11pm cancellation text I had to send."</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:32px;color:var(--tx-soft);font-size:16px;">
        You're already great at the adjustment / the manual therapy / the consult. The leak is operational —
        the work that happens when you're with another patient and nobody is texting the one who didn't come back.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we run -->
  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow" style="text-align:center;">What we run for you</p>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:32px;">Five systems. Wraps around Jane App. Respects College rules.</h2>
      <div class="ai-grid-2">

        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>1. Reactivation &amp; rebooking sequences</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">Pulls your inactive list from Jane App on a schedule (90d / 120d / 180d / 1yr). Sends the right SMS/email at the right interval — different copy for MVA patients, WSIB claims, wellness-care drop-offs, and one-and-done consults.</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Inactive sweep across 4 cohorts</li>
            <li>Care-plan-aware sequences (not generic blasts)</li>
            <li>Rebooking link pre-filled to your Jane calendar</li>
            <li>CCO / College of Physiotherapists advertising rules respected</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>2. 5-minute lead response</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">Every new lead from your website, Google profile, Instagram DM, or phone gets an SMS within 60 seconds. Books straight into Jane. Routes to your phone if it needs a human. No more "I'll call them tomorrow."</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>SMS within 60 seconds of inquiry</li>
            <li>Multi-channel: web, GMB, Instagram, missed call</li>
            <li>Direct booking into Jane App calendar</li>
            <li>Handoff to practitioner phone for complex cases</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>3. Care plan completion automation</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">Tracks every patient's place in their plan. Triggers a reminder 72 hours after a missed appointment. Sends an educational SMS if they're falling behind. Re-engages drop-offs at visit 4, 8, 12 — different message at each step.</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Plan-progress visibility per patient</li>
            <li>Missed-appointment recovery sequence</li>
            <li>Educational re-engagement at drop-off points</li>
            <li>Owner dashboard with completion %</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>4. Review velocity (College-compliant)</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">SMS review request after the 3rd visit, not the 1st (College rules — and 3rd-visit reviews are higher-quality). Negative feedback intercepted privately. Average practice adds 25–40 Google reviews in 90 days.</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Timed for the 3rd-visit checkpoint</li>
            <li>CCO / OPA advertising rules respected</li>
            <li>Negative feedback to private inbox</li>
            <li>Review reply automation in your tone</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>5. Owner dashboard + reporting</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">One screen. Reactivations this month, new lead response time, care plan completion, review velocity, total recovered revenue. Monthly PDF for your accountant or your accountability buddy.</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>The 3 R's at a glance</li>
            <li>New patient response time metric</li>
            <li>Per-modality breakdown (chiro / physio / RMT)</li>
            <li>Monthly PDF report</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ai-card" style="border-color:var(--accent);background:var(--accent-soft);">
          <h3 style="color:var(--accent);">Jane App–native.</h3>
          <p>Your team keeps using Jane the way they do today. We integrate via the Jane App API + a thin layer of automation. Direct billing, ROFs, charting — none of it changes. We only fill the gaps Jane was never designed to fill.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing teaser (same 3 tiers, different "most start here" callout) -->
  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow" style="text-align:center;">Simple pricing</p>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;">Three tiers. Cancel after 90 days.</h2>
      <p style="text-align:center;color:var(--tx-soft);margin-bottom:32px;max-width:640px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">Most chiro / physio practices start on Plug The Leak — your bottleneck is usually reactivation, not lead volume.</p>
      <div class="ai-tiers">

        <article class="ai-tier ai-tier-featured" style="--tier-tag:'Most chiros start here';">
          <h3>Plug The Leak</h3>
          <p class="ai-tier-tagline">Stop bleeding</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price">$1,497<span style="font-size:16px;font-weight:500;color:var(--tx-soft);">/mo</span></p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price-sub">+ $1,500 one-time setup</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Reactivation sweep across 4 cohorts</li>
            <li>5-minute lead response (SMS + email)</li>
            <li>SMS appointment reminders</li>
            <li>Google review automation</li>
            <li>Owner dashboard</li>
            <li>Jane App integration</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a free audit →</a>
        </article>

        <article class="ai-tier">
          <h3>Fill The Calendar</h3>
          <p class="ai-tier-tagline">Plus growth</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price">$2,497<span style="font-size:16px;font-weight:500;color:var(--tx-soft);">/mo</span></p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price-sub">+ $2,500 one-time setup</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Everything in Plug The Leak</li>
            <li>Care plan completion automation</li>
            <li>Two-way SMS team inbox</li>
            <li>Monthly content (newsletter + 4 social posts)</li>
            <li>Google Ads management (lite)</li>
            <li>Quarterly strategy review</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="/services/">Compare tiers →</a>
        </article>

        <article class="ai-tier">
          <h3>Run It For Me</h3>
          <p class="ai-tier-tagline">Done-for-you, end-to-end</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price">$4,997<span style="font-size:16px;font-weight:500;color:var(--tx-soft);">/mo</span></p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price-sub">+ $5,000 one-time setup</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Everything in Fill The Calendar</li>
            <li>AI voice receptionist for after-hours</li>
            <li>Custom n8n integrations</li>
            <li>Dedicated ops contact</li>
            <li>Weekly check-in</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="/services/">Compare tiers →</a>
        </article>

      </div>
      <p style="text-align:center;color:var(--tx-soft);margin-top:24px;font-size:14px;">All prices CAD. No long contracts. CCO + College of Physiotherapists rules respected.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="ai-section-tight">
    <div class="ai-wrap ai-narrow" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2>30-min audit. No deck.</h2>
      <p class="ai-lead">We screen-share Jane with you, look at the inactives, and tell you what would move the most revenue this quarter.</p>
      <div class="ai-cta-row">
        <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book the audit →</a>
        <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="/about/">About Aman</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
